item.title: Titan
item.description: Wikipedia # https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Titan_(moon) Maps # Quadrangles # Titan’s quadrangles haven’t been defined at the time of writing. We can assume that they should be named “St” can be inferred from the other jovian and saturnian moons such as Europa (Je), Ganymede (Jg), Enceladus (Se)… So Titan should be St. Regarding the quadrangles definition, I overlapped the traditional division into 15 quadrangles of the Jovian moons (and other moons/small planets) found here: https://ntrs.
